          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2929808",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2929808",
                "title": "Figure 1",
                "abstract": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A capsule and its properties "
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Define the size of the two hemispheres forming the ends of a capsule with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncapsule/1523926-capradius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. Because the cylindrical body of the capsule stretches between the its two hemispherical ends, its circular cross section in the x- and z-axis dimensions has the same radius. Define the capsuleâ€™s extent in the z-axis dimension of its local coordinate space with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncapsule/1522789-height"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. To change the orientation of a capsule, adjust the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnnode/1407964-transform"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of the node containing the capsule geometry."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Control the level of detail with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncapsule/1523697-heightsegmentcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncapsule/1523561-capsegmentcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncapsule/1522789-height"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties. Higher radial and cap segment counts create smoother curves for the cylinderâ€™s circular sides and hemispherical ends. A higher segment count in any direction produces more vertices, which can improve rendering quality for certain lighting models or custom shader effects, but at a cost to rendering performance."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
